# Git Workflow Skill

## Binding Directives

### Commit Discipline
- One logical unit per commit (one feature, one bug fix, one decision)
- Never mix unrelated changes in a single commit
- Exclude all generated files: `bin/`, `obj/`, `.next/`, `dist/`, `*.egg-info`, `.next-dev/`, `.playwright-artifacts/`
- Exclude temp outputs: `.pytest_cache/`, `__pycache__/`, `*.pyc`, `.tsbuildinfo`

### Commit Message Format
```
[SCOPE]: Brief one-line summary

- Detailed explanation of what changed
- Each change on its own line
- Link to decision/spec/task ID if applicable

Co-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>
```

### Pre-Commit Verification
```bash
git status  # Verify no build artifacts are staged
git diff --cached  # Review all staged changes
```

### Push Discipline
- **Every commit must be pushed within the session it's created**
- Never accumulate more than 3 unpushed commits
- Push at natural break points: after spec approval, after tests pass, after decision merge
- Push immediately: `git push origin <feature-branch>`

### Handling Feature Branches
```bash
# If origin is ahead of your feature branch:
git fetch origin
git rebase origin/main
git push origin --force-with-lease <feature-branch>

# Never use merge, always rebase
```

### Merging to Main
- **Run full test/lint/typecheck suite before merge:**
  ```bash
  npm run build:web && npm run test:api && npm run test:worker && npm run lint:web && npm run typecheck:web
  ```
- **Rebase to main:**
  ```bash
  git rebase origin/main
  git push origin --force-with-lease <feature-branch>
  ```
- **Merge strategy:** Squash-and-merge via GitHub PR (never manual merge commit)
- **Backup branch before delete:** `git tag feature/<name>-backup <sha>`

### Squad File Discipline
- All `.squad/` files must be committed together in atomic batch
- Commit pattern: `docs: [describe what the decision/log records]`
- Never leave `.squad/` files untracked for more than one session
- Append-only files use union merge strategy (configured in `.gitattributes`)

### Line Ending Safety
- Config: `git config core.safecrlf true` (prevents CRLF leaks)
- `.gitattributes` enforces `eol=lf` on all source files
- Run `git diff --check` before committing to catch whitespace issues

## When to Escalate
- Branch diverges >50 commits from main → Kirk decomposes into smaller merge windows
- Merge conflict on `.squad/` file → Kirk manually resolves (union merge catches append-only issues)
- Tracked artifact discovered after merge → Kirk branches back and removes (fast-forward main)
- Line-ending violations at CI → Reject PR; require local reset and re-push

